File: Cabinet has directed Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan to prepare an updated report on SAA after his department denied a R10-billion bailout. JOHANNESBURG - Government ministers have met with trade union leaders to discuss the future of the embattled South African Airways. Cabinet discussed how the unions will work with the government during the business rescue process to ensure the wellbeing of workers. Government has reiterated that it won't provide more money to the airline. READ: Unions reject SAA retrenchment proposal Last week a request by business rescue practitioners for a further R10-million was turned down. Labour unions at SAA have been invited to submit restructuring proposals for the national carrier and the future of jobs going forward. The unions have already rejected a proposal to cut jobs.